and Columbus

00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:00.734 position:16% line:89% align:start
have commissioned works.

00:19:00.767 --> 00:19:03.934 position:13% line:83% align:start
We've had orders from royal
families around the world.

00:19:03.968 --> 00:19:05.200 position:47% line:89% align:start
In that case...

00:19:05.234 --> 00:19:06.901 position:24% line:89% align:start
Why'd you look concerned?

00:19:06.934 --> 00:19:10.133 position:16% line:89% align:start
Well, the date says 1436.

00:19:10.167 --> 00:19:13.934 position:16% line:83% align:start
Let's see, now if I remember
my history correctly...

00:19:13.968 --> 00:19:15.601 position:55% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:19:15.634 --> 00:19:19.601 position:10% line:83% align:start
But she was burnt at the stake
in Rouen's market square in...

00:19:19.634 --> 00:19:21.067 position:27% line:89% align:start
That is correct.

00:19:21.100 --> 00:19:23.701 position:16% line:89% align:start
She met her fate in 1431.

00:19:23.734 --> 00:19:27.100 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:19:27.133 --> 00:19:28.734 position:10% line:89% align:start
But according to this ledger,

00:19:28.767 --> 00:19:33.234 position:7% line:83% align:start
this stone was made five years
after her very public execution.

00:19:33.267 --> 00:19:36.934 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yet somehow commissioned
by Jeanne of Arc herself.

00:19:36.968 --> 00:19:38.567 position:44% line:83% align:start
All:
[ Gasping ]

00:19:38.601 --> 00:19:49.133 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:19:49.167 --> 00:19:51.367 position:35% line:83% align:start
Hopefully that helped
a little bit?

00:19:51.400 --> 00:19:53.334 position:19% line:83% align:start
It helped,
more than a little.

00:19:53.367 --> 00:19:55.701 position:5% line:77% align:start
We're eternally grateful.
We are!

00:19:55.734 --> 00:19:57.834 position:16% line:89% align:start
Thank you so much, Arya!

00:19:57.868 --> 00:20:00.934 position:27% line:83% align:start
You're all very welcome.
Say.

00:20:00.968 --> 00:20:05.033 position:33% line:83% align:start
Why not stay the night
before heading out?

00:20:05.067 --> 00:20:07.033 position:16% line:83% align:start
I appreciate
the generous offer.

00:20:07.067 --> 00:20:08.601 position:5% line:89% align:start
But time is of the essence.

00:20:08.634 --> 00:20:10.534 position:5% line:89% align:start
We must take our leave.

00:20:10.567 --> 00:20:12.701 position:52% line:83% align:start
Oh, I see.
I understand.

00:20:12.734 --> 00:20:14.334 position:38% line:83% align:start
Please, do take care
of yourselves.

00:20:14.367 --> 00:20:17.067 position:44% line:83% align:start
And I shall pray
for your safe passage.

00:20:23.601 --> 00:20:26.167 position:72% line:83% align:start
Fena!
Oh?

00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:27.834 position:5% line:89% align:start
Hang in there, okay?

00:20:27.868 --> 00:20:35.968 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:45.534 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:20:46.634 --> 00:20:48.634 position:24% line:89% align:start
[ Waves crashing ]

00:20:52.267 --> 00:20:54.133 position:55% line:83% align:start
Yukimaru:
You'll catch cold.

00:20:56.968 --> 00:20:59.367 position:38% line:83% align:start
They sure were nice,
weren't they?

00:20:59.400 --> 00:21:03.000 position:52% line:83% align:start
They were.
Very pleasant people, indeed.

00:21:05.000 --> 00:21:07.334 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yukimaru.

00:21:07.367 --> 00:21:10.100 position:5% line:83% align:start
Truth is, I've actually
heard it before.

00:21:10.133 --> 00:21:12.434 position:19% line:89% align:start
